      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Mary Bachman is a member of the Antique Comb Collectors Club and editor of their newsletter.   The club was formed as the Antique Comb Collectors Club (ACCC or AC3), and later became the Antique Comb Collectors Club International (ACCCI).  She is 
		also the author of <emph render="italic">Collector's Guide to Hair Combs: Identification and Values</emph> (1998).</p>
		</bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
			<p>The <emph render="bold">Mary Bachman Papers</emph> contains Antique Comb Collectors Club material, correspondence, 
			photographs, printed material, subject files, and videorecordings.</p>
			
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Antique Comb Collectors Club material</emph> conains address lists, communications with 
			members and the Board of Directors, issues of the club newsletter (a few in hard copy, with a complete set on 
			CD), club documents and publicity, and so on.  </p>

         <p><emph render="bold">Correspondence</emph> contains general correspondene with other collectors and a small 
			amount with sellers.</p>

         <p><emph render="bold">Photographs</emph> consists primarily of photographs of other collectors' combs.  Many are 
			labeled on the back.</p>

         <p><emph render="bold">Printed material</emph> contains clippings by and about Bachman and other comb 
			collectors, including Jen Cruse and Belva Green, as well as pieces on combs and comb collecting generally.</p>

         <p><emph render="bold">Subject files</emph> were undifferentiated when received, and have been sorted by topic. 
			Most of these have to do with various materials used in comb-making and manufacture, including horn, ivory, jet, 
			and plastics.</p>

         <p><emph render="bold">Videorecordings</emph> contains "How to make a celluloid comb" and a VHS tape of a European television program.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
